description: mXparser is a super easy, rich, fast and highly flexible math expression parser library (parser and evaluator of mathematical expressions / formulas provided as plain text / string). Software delivers easy to use API for JAVA, Android and C# .NET/MONO (Common Language Specification compliant: F#, Visual Basic, C++/CLI). *** If you finnd the software useful donation is something you might consider: http://mathparser.org/donate/ ***
releaseNotes: v.4.1.1 Fixed: checkSyntax() returns true "already checked no errors" #75. v.4.1.0 Aeries - Major update: Various numeral systems + Working with digits (number of digits, digit at position), Leading zeros, Prime factorization, Not-a-Number support, Variadic or + and + xor, Other nice functions (argmin, argmax, root, mode, median, coalesce), Percentage '%' as operator, Alternative syntax for derivative, Built-in tokens manipulation, Interacting with expression tokens.
summary: mXparser is a super easy, rich, fast and highly flexible math expression parser library (parser and evaluator of mathematical expressions / formulas provided as plain text / string). Expression parser comes with extensive documentation, easy to follow tutorial, "Hello World!" projects for different languages explained with many screenshots, and finally - last, but not least - performance test summary. Formula evaluator is distributed under "Simplified BSD license", which means software is completely free.
